Package: testreg
Title: Bayesian Meta-Regression with Stan and NIMBLE Backends
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("JoonHo", "Lee", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   email = "joonho@example.com")
Description: Fits random-effects Bayesian meta-regression models using either
    Stan (via 'cmdstanr') or NIMBLE as the computational backend. Provides a
    unified interface for model fitting, convergence diagnostics, posterior
    summaries, posterior predictive checks, and visualization including forest
    plots, caterpillar plots, and traceplots.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    posterior,
    stats
Suggests:
    cmdstanr,
    rstan,
    nimble,
    bayesplot,
    coda,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
